On 2/3/23, the operation also emailed and reported their current process for running background checks for new hires is listed below. These steps are completed for ALL employees, contractors and anyone on the campus that has direct or indirect involvement with children:
	All employees are submitted through the Texas Health & Human Services Child Care Licensing (form that is filled out and submitted by HR attached) 
	They also use a standardized program, PreCheck, that verifies positive identification of the individual, maiden/alias search, employment verification, education verification, sex offender registry list, national criminal history, statewide criminal search, county level criminal history, and SanctionCheck screening (form outlining the process is attached) 
	PreCheck transport package is also submitted for anyone operating a vehicle or transporting children. 

They reported moving forward they will request background checks from facilities for any employees they share or will request new background checks."
